      "reviewer_notes": "Gate 2 (Trust Boundary): This finding requires a compromised or buggy local Execution Layer to send data column sidecars with invalid inclusion proofs. The code at fork_choice_store/src/store.rs:2185 intentionally skips inclusion proof verification for ExecutionLayer origin (`if !origin.is_from_el()`), while P2P-sourced data columns are fully verified. According to BUG_BOUNTY_SCOPE.json trust_assumptions, the Engine API has trust_level 'SEMI_TRUSTED' with note: 'attacks requiring a compromised local EL may be considered conditional or lower severity'. The 01e property PROP-6a4369e9-inv-018 from outputs/01e_PARTIAL_W2B3_1771748669.json requires 'Merkle inclusion proof must link kzg_commitments to the block body_root' for P2P-sourced data (attacker_controlled: true). However, Phase 03's violation occurs only on the trusted EL path, not the untrusted P2P path which is correctly validated. The P2P gossip validation (line 2185-2192) enforces the spec requirement for untrusted sources. This is a defense-in-depth gap requiring compromised trusted infrastructure, outside the security model per PROP-6a4369e9-asm-002.",
      "spec_reference": "Merkle inclusion proof must link kzg_commitments to the block body_root. (01e_PARTIAL_W2B3_1771748669.json, line 444)"
